  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2007-09-19",
    "date": "2008-01-30T20:05:40Z",
    "text": "Homeowners' Emergency Mortgage Assistance Act - Directs the Secretary of Housing and Urban Development to establish a mortgage emergency assistance program for qualifying homeowners with National Housing Act-insured mortgages who are temporarily unable to meet their obligations due to financial hardship beyond their control.\n\nRequires: (1) homeowner repayment of such assistance and interest; and (2) certain conditions to be met before legal action may be taken against a qualifying homeowner, including providing the homeowner with program notice."
  },
